Program: Omnibus
Title: Engels in Manchester
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jm3
Last Broadcast Date: 02 May 1989
A look at the contribution German social scientist Friedrich Engels made to the political theories of 'The Communist Manifesto' and 'The Condition of the Working Class in England', which was based on personal observations from the time in which he lived in Manchester.